title: All mammals have two ears that are pretty similar. But insects have separately evolved ears 19 different times, just about everywhere on their bodies. It's easy for that to happen in insects, because they have lots of cells that are specialized for detecting loud changes? And all that happens to happen is for some of those cells to become more sensitive.
pid: 6038c179-ce9a-477f-b7f0-ece9504ea9c0
